2C%20not%20surprisingly%2C%20takes%20up%20the%20biggest%20chunk%20of%20my%20time.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20I%20learned%20that%20a%20new%20iOS%20app%20called%20Steppin%20%E2%80%94%20created%20by%20the%20Kayak%20cofounder%20Paul%20English%20%E2%80%94%20aims%20to%20help%20people%20%26quot%3Bescape%20the%20scroll%2C%26quot%3B%20I%20was%20intrigued.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%2228e2cb2b-9532-416d-ad3f-b8a3bd98b285%5C%22%3EI%20tested%20the%20app%20for%20a%20week%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3ESteppin%20combines%20the%20goals%20of%20clocking%20steps%20and%20limiting%20screen%20time.%20The%20more%20steps%20you%20take%2C%20the%20more%20time%20you%20are%20granted%20to%20use%20your%20restricted%20apps.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EEach%20user%20can%20set%20their%20own%20parameters.%20I%20decided%20to%20restrict%20two%20of%20my%20most%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fsocial-media-dead-instagram-tiktok-bereal-replaced-group-chats-messaging-2023-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Etime-draining%20apps%3A%20Instagram%20and%20TikTok%3C%2Fa%3E.%20For%20every%20100%20steps%20taken%2C%20I%20granted%20myself%20one%20minute%20of%20usage%20on%20my%20restricted%20apps.%20My%20earned%20time%20would%20reset%20every%20day.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221440%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20screenshot%20of%20Steppin'%20app.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F67a19060eb4be2fff9a360df%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221080%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EUsers%20can%20choose%20which%20apps%20to%20restrict%20(left)%20and%20decide%20their%20limits.%3Cp%3EErin%20Liam%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EI%20spent%20my%20first%20day%20working%20from%20home.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENormally%2C%20I%20use%20my%20evenings%20to%20unwind%20by%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fdad-worries-australia-social-media-ban-will-negative-impact-teenager-2024-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Escrolling%20social%20media%3C%2Fa%3E.%20But%20on%20that%20day%2C%20by%205%20p.m.%2C%20I%20had%20only%20tracked%20200%20steps.%20With%20only%20two%20minutes%20to%20scroll%2C%20I%20decided%20to%20walk%20to%20a%20nearby%20park%20instead.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20I%20was%20done%2C%20I%20had%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhow-five-hundred-extra-steps-per-day-live-longer-2023-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ewalked%20more%20than%202%2C000%20steps%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20the%20equivalent%20of%2020%20minutes%20of%20screen%20time.%20Seeing%20the%20number%20jump%20on%20the%20app%20gave%20me%20a%20dopamine%20rush.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222250%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Screenshot%20of%20Steppin'%20app%2C%20showing%20time%20setting.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F67a190a87bb3f854015b9ebc%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%223000%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EUsers%20can%20choose%20how%20much%20of%20their%20earned%20time%20to%20use%20on%20their%20restricted%20apps.%3Cp%3EErin%20Liam%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EAt%20the%20end%20of%20the%20day%2C%20I%20had%20built%20up%20credit%20and%20could%20choose%20how%20much%20of%20my%20earned%20time%20to%20spend%20on%20my%20restricted%20apps.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20used%20the%20app%20for%20a%20week.%20The%20biggest%20change%20was%20that%20I%20stopped%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhow-ceo-reduced-phone-use-deceased-stress-2023-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Escrolling%20social%20media%20as%20soon%20as%20I%20woke%20up%3C%2Fa%3E%3B%20I%20couldn't%2C%20because%20I%20hadn't%20clocked%20the%20required%20steps%20for%20that%20day.%20I%20felt%20refreshed%20and%20ended%20up%20with%20more%20productive%20mornings.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBy%20the%20end%20of%20the%20week%2C%20my%20average%20screen%20time%20dropped%20by%20almost%20two%20hours.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22fe4381a9-9054-4df2-a4e1-77559589f5dc%5C%22%3EHow%20it%20works%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3ESteppin%20is%20not%20the%20first%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcure-for-doomscrolling-shaming-your-friends-screentime-app-2024-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eapp%20designed%20to%20curb%20screen%20time%3C%2Fa%3E.%20The%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fguides%2Fparenting%2Fqustodio-review%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EQustodio%3C%2Fa%3E%20parental%20app%2C%20released%20in%202012%2C%20allows%20parents%20to%20block%20apps%20and%20set%20daily%20screen%20time%20limits.%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fapps-that-changed-peoples-lives-2016-7%23forest-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EForest%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20released%20the%20following%20year%2C%20grows%20virtual%20trees%20during%20focus%20sessions.%20If%20users%20leave%20the%20app%2C%20the%20tree%20starts%20to%20die.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThere%20are%20also%20built-in%20apps%20that%20allow%20users%20to%20set%20daily%20limits.%20Apple%20Screen%20Time%20is%20a%20feature%20on%20iPhones%2C%20and%20Digital%20Wellbeing%2C%20developed%20by%20Google%2C%20is%20on%20most%20Android%20devices.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPaul%20English%2C%20the%20CEO%20of%20Boston%20Venture%20Studio%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Eand%20the%20cofounder%20of%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Ethe%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftravel-budget-calculator-millennial-inflation-depressing-kayak-2023-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Etravel%20search%20engine%20Kayak%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20told%20Business%20Insider%20the%20idea%20for%20Steppin%20was%20sparked%20on%20a%20family%20trip%20to%20Spain.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDuring%20the%20trip%2C%20English's%20then-fianc%C3%A9e%2C%20Rachel%20Cohen%2C%20and%20his%20son%2C%20Mike%20English%2C%20discussed%20ways%20to%20reduce%20screen%20time.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20credited%20the%20other%20two%20for%20the%20idea.%20%26quot%3BThe%20idea%20really%20came%20from%20Michael%20and%20Rachel%20more%20than%20me.%20I%20was%20really%20excited%20about%20that%20and%20I%20said%2C%20we%20gotta%20do%20this%2C%20let's%20build%20it%2C%20let's%20build%20it%2C%20let's%20put%20a%20team%20together%20because%20I%20think%20it's%20a%20really%20good%20idea%2C%26quot%3B%20English%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThere%20should%20be%20something%20outside%20of%20your%20phone%20to%20manage%20a%20phone%20addiction%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20younger%20English%2C%2029%2C%20a%20product%20manager%20and%20designer%20at%20Boston%20Venture%20Studio%2C%20told%20BI.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWalking%20is%20obviously%20something%20that%20almost%20everybody%20does.%20So%20that%20felt%20like%20a%20perfect%20combination%20of%20physical%20and%20mental%20well-being%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said%20of%20the%20inspiration%20behind%20the%20app.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20app%20was%20released%20last%20month%20and%20is%20free%20on%20the%20App%20Store%2C%20although%20they%20are%20planning%20to%20charge%20an%20annual%20subscription%20fee%20of%20around%20%2420.%20Steppin%20is%20not%20yet%20available%20on%20Google%20Play%2C%20but%20Android%20users%20can%20sign%20up%20for%20its%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.steppin.net%2Fandroid%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ewaitlist%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20have%20several%20thousand%20downloads%2C%20which%20is%20great%20since%20we%20just%20released%20the%20app%20a%20couple%20weeks%20ago%20and%20we%20have%20not%20started%20any%20marketing%20yet%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20elder%20English%20said.%20He%20declined%20to%20give%20a%20specific%20download%20count.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22d6c6cf8a-ba93-49fe-abda-cbda2211e4d4%5C%22%3EWhy%20Steppin%20might%20%E2%80%94%20or%20might%20not%20%E2%80%94%20work%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EPamela%20Rutledge%2C%20a%20media%20psychologist%20and%20the%20director%20of%20the%20Media%20Psychology%20Research%20Center%2C%20an%20independent%20research%20organization%20in%20California%2C%20said%20that%20Steppin%20could%20appeal%20to%20users%20who%20enjoy%20setting%20short-term%20goals%20with%20immediate%20rewards.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAssuming%20that%20screen%20time%20is%20a%20%26quot%3Bhigh-reward%26quot%3B%20activity%2C%20pairing%20it%20with%20a%20%26quot%3Bgood%20for%20you%26quot%3B%20behavior%20can%20help%20people%20overcome%20inertia%2C%20she%20told%20BI.%20%26quot%3BThis%20app%20might%20act%20as%20a%20gentle%20reminder%20to%20get%20moving%2C%20but%20more%20importantly%2C%20it%20breaks%20habitual%20behaviors%20and%20shifts%20attention%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20Rutledge%20said%20that%20the%20app's%20effectiveness%20will%20depend%20on%20the%20user's%20motivations%2C%20adding%20that%20users%20may%20become%20frustrated%20or%20lose%20interest%20once%20its%20novelty%20wears%20off.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESome%20experts%20also%20expressed%20concerns%20about%20a%20feature%20that%20allows%20users%20to%20override%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fbroke-parenting-rules-allowed-unlimited-screen-time-2024-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Escreen%20time%20restrictions%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20emergencies.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMelissa%20Hunt%2C%20a%20clinical%20psychologist%20at%20the%20University%20of%20Pennsylvania%2C%20said%20the%20app%20might%20be%20effective%20initially%20in%20making%20people%20more%20aware%20of%20their%20screen%20time%20by%20helping%20them%20be%20mindful%2C%20she%20said.%20%26quot%3BBut%20overall%2C%20technology%20solutions%20to%20technology%20problems%20are%20always%20going%20to%20be%20inherently%20problematic%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMike%20English%20said%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Ethe%20option%20to%20override%20restrictions%20was%20included%20to%20give%20users%20more%20flexibility.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20took%20self-discipline%20to%20stop%20myself%20from%20overriding%20restrictions%20when%20I%20ran%20out%20of%20earned%20time.%20But%20being%20restricted%20from%20using%20social%20media%20didn't%20stop%20me%20from%20fiddling%20with%20my%20phone%20