ed%20to%20be%20moisture-resistant.%20Pakkawood%20is%20a%20composite%20material%20often%20used%20for%20knife%20handles%20that%20is%20made%20of%20wood%20and%20resin%20and%20is%20especially%20durable.%20Lastly%2C%20despite%20the%20fact%20that%20some%20knives%20are%20labeled%20dishwasher%20safe%2C%20you%20can%20preserve%20the%20longevity%20of%20your%20knives%20by%20hand%20washing%20and%20drying.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22203b4de4-aa9a-4167-ab63-e611041fa61e%5C%22%20data-toc-label%3D%5C%22How%20we%20test%5C%22%3EHow%20we%20tested%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Side%20by%20side%20images%20of%20five%20steak%20knives%20from%20different%20brands%20and%20a%20single%20steak%20knife%20being%20measured%20with%20a%20tape-measure.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F64f77a7e1b7ced0019c874ec%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22900%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EAfter%20testing%2011%20sets%20of%20steak%20knives%2C%20we%20found%20that%20hand%20feel%20and%20initial%20sharpness%20are%20two%20key%20factors.%3Cp%3EAndrea%20Wawrzyn%2FBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EBefore%20and%20after%20each%20of%20the%20following%20tests%2C%20we%20washed%20and%20dried%20the%20knives%20by%20hand.%20We%20then%20performed%20each%20test%20a%20second%20time%20to%20see%20if%20the%20knives%20had%20become%20noticeably%20duller%20after%20use%20and%20cleaning.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EPaper%20test%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20We%20used%20each%20knife%20to%20cut%20through%20a%20sheet%20of%20printer%20paper%20to%20see%20if%20it%20made%20clean%2C%20smooth%20cuts%20or%20tore.%20We%20also%20noted%20whether%20we%20had%20to%20apply%20pressure%20to%20start%20the%20cuts%20or%20if%20the%20knives%20were%20able%20to%20cut%20through%20it%20easily.%20This%20revealed%20how%20sharp%20the%20knives%20were%20out%20of%20the%20box.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ESteak%20test%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20We%20cooked%204%20pounds%20of%20skirt%20steak%20(one%20of%20the%20toughest%20cuts)%20and%2012%20links%20of%20Italian%20sausage%20and%20used%20each%20knife%20to%20cut%20through%20both.%20We%20noted%20whether%20they%20made%20clean%20cuts%20through%20the%20meat%2C%20or%20tore%20it%20leaving%20jagged%20edges.%20All%20of%20the%20meat%20was%20cut%20on%20stoneware%20dinner%20plates%2C%20which%20can%20be%20rougher%20on%20knives%20than%20other%20cutting%20surfaces%2C%20like%20a%20cutting%20board.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EEase%20of%20use%3A%20%3C%2Fstrong%3EDuring%20our%20cutting%20tests%2C%20we%20considered%20how%20the%20knives%20felt%20to%20hold%20and%20cut%20with%2C%20if%20they%20were%20comfortable%20in%20the%20hand%2C%20and%20whether%20they%20felt%20secure.%20We%20evaluated%20the%20size%20of%20the%20blade%2C%20handle%2C%20and%20full%20construction%20to%20determine%20how%20that%20affected%20the%20knife's%20performance%20and%20weight.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%220553bb83-2152-41df-8df2-4c14439de797%5C%22%20data-toc-label%3D%5C%22FAQs%5C%22%3EFAQs%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Ch3%3E%3Cstrong%3ECan%20you%20sharpen%20steak%20knives%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh3%3E%3Cp%3EAbsolutely.%20How%20you%20sharpen%20them%20depends%20on%20whether%20your%20knives%20are%20serrated%20or%20straight-edged.%20Straight-edged%20knives%20can%20be%20sharpened%20using%20any%20of%20the%20methods%20you%20would%20use%20on%20a%20chef's%20knife%3B%20a%20handheld%20sharpener%2C%20a%20whetstone%2C%20or%20a%20honing%20steel%20(check%20out%20our%20picks%20for%20the%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fguides%2Fkitchen%2Fbest-knife-sharpener%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ebest%20knife%20sharpeners%3C%2Fa%3E).%20Serrated%20blades%20are%20more%20difficult%20to%20sharpen%20at%20home%20and%20may%20need%20to%20be%20handled%20by%20a%20professional.%20Check%20with%20the%20knife%20manufacturer%20for%20instructions%20and%20recommendations%20for%20sharpening%20your%20particular%20knives.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch3%3E%3Cstrong%3EAre%20straight-edged%20knives%20better%20than%20serrated%20knives%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh3%3E%3Cp%3EThat%20is%20a%20matter%20of%20opinion%2C%20and%20good%20quality%20knives%20will%20cut%20meat%20well%20whether%20the%20blade%20is%20serrated%20or%20not.%20Straight-edged%20knives%20are%20designed%20to%20slice%20through%20meat%20smoothly%20with%20little%20resistance%2C%20while%20serrated%20blades%20can%20tear%20through%20meat%20and%20require%20you%20to%20use%20a%20back-and-forth%20sawing%20motion.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch3%3E%3Cstrong%3ECan%20you%20put%20steak%20knives%20in%20the%20dishwasher%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh3%3E%3Cp%3EHand%20washing%20and%20drying%20steak%20knives%20will%20give%20them%20the%20longest%20life%20possible.%20While%20some%20of%20the%20knives%20we%20tested%20are%20dishwasher%20safe%2C%20we%20don't%20recommend%20it.%20Running%20sharp%20knives%20through%20the%20dishwasher%20cycle%20will%20dull%20the%20blades%2C%20meaning%20you'll%20have%20to%20sharpen%20them%20more%20often%20or%20replace%20them%20sooner.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch3%3E%3Cstrong%3EHow%20should%20you%20store%20steak%20knives%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh3%3E%3Cp%3EWe%20recommend%20storing%20steak%20knives%20in%20a%20knife%20block%2C%20on%20a%20magnetic%20strip%2C%20or%20with%20a%20sheath%20to%20keep%20the%20blades%20in%20good%20cutting%20condition.%20Some%20steak%20knives%20ship%20with%20their%20own%20storage%20boxes%20or%20blocks.%20You%20should%20avoid%20storing%20them%20loose%20in%20a%20utensil%20drawer.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3EBest%20overall%3A%20Material%20The%20Table%20Knives%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%223017%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20steak%20knife%20from%20cookware%20brand%20Material%20with%20a%20blue%20handle%20on%20a%20wooden%20cutting%20board.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F64f76f4f1b7ced0019c86a7e%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%222262%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EWe%20think%20these%20affordable