C%20to%20discuss%20three%20rules%20that%20would%20affect%20people's%202024%20tax%20returns%20that%20they%20might%20not%20know%20about.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22c81fabb0-abe2-4035-a2a5-19f37d0efdf1%5C%22%3E1.%20Inflation-adjusted%20tax%20brackets%20and%20standard%20deductions%20have%20changed%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EOne%20change%20that%20Richards%20noted%20happens%20every%20year%20but%20is%20still%20worth%20paying%20attention%20to.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20IRS%20updates%20tax%20brackets%20and%20standard%20deduction%20amounts%20every%20year%20for%20inflation%2C%26quot%3B%20Richards%20said.%20%26quot%3BTaxpayers%20can%20expect%20to%20have%20slightly%20different%20tax%20brackets%2C%20and%20the%20standard%20deduction%20rate%20has%20gone%20up%20%24750%20for%20those%20filing%20single%20or%20married%20filing%20separately%20and%20%241%2C500%20for%20those%20married%20filing%20jointly.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20tax%20bracket%20adjustments%20for%202024%20can%20be%20found%20on%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.irs.gov%2Fnewsroom%2Firs-provides-tax-inflation-adjustments-for-tax-year-2024%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EIRS%20website%3C%2Fa%3E.%20You%20may%20end%20up%20paying%20a%20lower%20or%20higher%20rate%20than%20in%20previous%20years.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIf%20your%20income%20stays%20the%20same%20from%202023%20to%202024%2C%20you%20may%20end%20up%20owing%20less%20in%20taxes%20because%20of%20inflation%20adjustments%2C%26quot%3B%20Richards%20said.%20%26quot%3BThese%20adjustments%20raised%20both%20the%20tax%20bracket%20thresholds%20and%20standard%20deductions.%20So%20even%20with%20identical%20earnings%2C%20your%20total%20tax%20bill%20could%20be%20lower%20in%202024%20than%20it%20was%20in%202023.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20you%20find%20yourself%20in%20a%20higher%20tax%20bracket%2C%20Richards%20recommended%20looking%20through%20your%20expenses%2C%20charitable%20donations%2C%20and%20deductions%20to%20see%20whether%20there's%20anything%20yo